// Storm's Beacon - the pilot episodes. A single-ship STORY universe on the universe_core
// mastlib (Mode: story, no admiral economy). Prof. Storm is VIRTUAL CREW: hail her on the
// Ultra-Beam (with no target selected) for each lead. She reveals the next site; you
// Engage-jump there from the Quests tab and scan the ancient ruin, then hail her again for
// the next heading. Two Storm-gated episodes here; the full campaign (reputation, XORN,
// crafting, Crazy Eddy) builds out from this spine - see STORMS_BEACON.md.

# Storm's Beacon
---
Display: Storms Beacon
---
Prof. Storm has a lead on the Beacon - an ancient signal buried in the ruins the old
giants left behind. Hail her for each heading, follow the clues, and stay a jump ahead of
whatever is hunting the same trail.

## Scenario
---
Mode: story
---

## Lifeforms

### Professor Storm (prof_storm)
---
Face: female
Roles: advisor
Scene: storm_hail
Color: #6cf
---
Expedition lead and xeno-archaeologist. A host-less advisor - hail her from anywhere on
the Ultra-Beam (no target selected) for the next lead on the Beacon.

## Dialogue

### Professor Storm (storm_hail)
---
Speaker: prof_storm
When: comms
---
% Storm here, Captain. What do you need?
% Go ahead - I'm knee-deep in old star charts.
% Talk to me. The trail's still warm.

- [Any word on the Beacon?](storm_hail) ; signal storm_check
- [Just checking in](storm_smalltalk)

### Professor Storm (storm_smalltalk)
---
Speaker: prof_storm
---
% Watch yourself out there. The Beacon isn't the only thing hunting these ruins.
% Keep the ship quiet and the sensors hot. We find it by being clever, not loud.

## Narrative

// The episodes nest under one arc via HEADING LEVELS: the arc is a `###` heading and each
// step is a `####` heading under it (local keys). quest_grant_amd builds the nested quest
// keys from the heading depth (`beacon_arc/<step>`, via quest_folder), so the Quests tab
// renders them as a collapsible tree under "The Beacon Hunt". `Then: reveal` and the mission
// code reference a step by its FULL path (`beacon_arc/ep1_scan`). (No `Parent:` field - that
// is the mission-tree COMPLETION flow, not display grouping; the win is on the terminal step.)

### The Beacon Hunt (beacon_arc)
---
Scope: shared
State: active
---
Prof. Storm's search for the Beacon - an ancient signal the old giants left buried in
their ruins. Hail her for each lead, follow the trail across the frontier, and read what
the dead stations still remember.

#### Contact Prof. Storm (briefing)
---
Scope: shared
State: active
When: signal storm_briefed
---
Hail Prof. Storm on the Ultra-Beam (no target selected) for your first lead on the Beacon.

#### Storm's First Lead (ep1_go)
---
Scope: shared
State: secret
When: reach 2, -1
Then: reveal beacon_arc/ep1_scan
---
Storm's first heading: an ancient Torgoth channel out at (2, -1), coreward past the old
marches. Engage the jump drive from your Quests tab and follow it in.

#### The Giant's House (ep1_scan)
---
Scope: shared
State: secret
When: scan 1 derelict
Pays: 150 credits
---
A Torgoth megastation from the age when the Torgoth were giants - docking throats wide
enough to swallow your ship. Bring the science array to bear and read what it remembers,
then hail Storm with what you find.

#### Storm's Next Lead (ep2_go)
---
Scope: shared
State: secret
When: reach 4, 1
Then: reveal beacon_arc/ep2_scan
---
Storm cross-referenced the megastation's glyphs: the trail runs on to the old Kralien
marches at (4, 1). Engage and jump.

#### The Kralien Archive (ep2_scan)
---
Scope: shared
State: secret
When: scan 1 derelict
Pays: 200 credits
---
A cold Kralien ruin, vast and silent, still holding one faint echo of the Beacon in its
archive. Scan it to pull the fragment from the dark - then hail Storm, because a fragment
is not the whole, and the trail runs deeper.

#### Storm's Last Lead (ep3_go)
---
Scope: shared
State: secret
When: reach 6, -2
Then: reveal beacon_arc/ep3_scan
---
Storm ran the Kralien fragment against the Torgoth glyphs and the two agree on one bearing:
a dead relay at (6, -2), right at the edge of the marches, where the Beacon's signal
begins. This is the origin. Engage and jump.

#### The Origin (ep3_scan)
---
Scope: shared
State: secret
When: scan 1 derelict
Win: true
Citation: The relay at the edge of the marches gave up the Beacon's origin at last - and Prof. Storm has what she came for. The Beacon is real, its bearing is logged, and this little ship flew home with a story the giants left behind.
---
A dead relay adrift at the very edge of the charted marches, older than the ruins that
pointed here - and still, faintly, the source of it all. Bring the science array to bear
and read the Beacon's origin from the dark.

## Regions

// Geography for the Beacon hunt: the old marches past the last charted buoy, where the
// giants of an earlier age left their megastations to rot. A nebula-heavy frontier - moody
// skybox, faint violet map wash, few ports - so the episode systems read as one distinct
// stretch of dark. Covers both ruin cells ((2,-1) and (4,1)) in one Chebyshev square.

### The Old Marches (old_marches)
---
Center: 3, 0
Radius: 3
Skybox: sky-neb2-rvb
Music: Artemis2
Color: #86c
Nebula mix: 55%
Station mix: 5%
Enemy mix: 10%
---
The frontier past the last charted buoy - the old marches, where the giants of an earlier
age left their megastations to rot in the drifting cloud. Nebulae everywhere, few ports,
and something always a jump behind you.

## Landmarks

### Torgoth Megastation (giants_house)
---
At: 2, -1
Kind: derelict
Terrain: nebula violet
Guards: skaraan 2
---
A derelict from the age of giants - a Torgoth station built to a scale no modern hull
needs, running dark for a thousand years, and still holding one faint echo of the Beacon.
Scavengers picked the trail up first - a light bounty-hunter wing loiters in the wreck's
shadow. (Guards: a skaraan fleet contests the ruin on arrival; clear or slip past to scan.)

### Kralien Ruin (kralien_ruin)
---
At: 4, 1
Kind: derelict
Terrain: asteroids
Guards: torgoth 3
---
A Kralien megastructure from their own age of giants, adrift and cold - and still
whispering one eleven-hundred-year-old word into the static. A Torgoth reclamation
party gutted the outer decks and lingers - they want the archive too. (Guards: a
torgoth fleet holds the ruin on arrival.)

### The Origin Relay (origin_relay)
---
At: 6, -2
Kind: derelict
Terrain: nebula red
Guards: skaraan 4
---
Older than the ruins that pointed here - a lone relay drifting at the edge of the charted
marches, wrapped in a bruise-red nebula, still faintly the source of the Beacon. Whatever
else has been hunting the trail got here first: a hard escort loiters in the murk.
